                    <span>If someone really want to know more in details about zeta function and its deep implication. Either this or Titchmarsh may do. Both books are excellent in this subject. Titchmarsh's book is more comprehensive but more difficult to read. Edward's one is more approachable and also it include some history and makes it more interersting. Anyway, both books are classics on this field.</span>
                  
              
